      "content": "It's not uncommon to feel a bit of heaviness and tingling after a long day in the sun, but it's crucial to monitor those symptoms closely. While coconut water will help with hydration, the sensation in your arm could be a sign of heat exhaustion or even heat stroke, which can be serious. I recommend cooling down immediately, taking a bath or shower, and drinking plenty of fluids. If the heaviness or tingling persists, seek medical attention right away. It's better to be safe and get checked out.",
