      "content": "You're right, hydration is key, and electrolytes will help replenish what you've lost. A cool room will also help your body recover from the heat. However, don't ignore the dizziness and confusion—these could be signs of a more serious condition. If you don't see an improvement in your symptoms within a few hours, or if they worsen, it's important to seek medical attention immediately. It's always better to be cautious with your health. Stay cool, stay hydrated, and keep an eye on how you feel. If you're not feeling better soon, don't hesitate to get help. Your health is the top priority.",
